_source.productDescription:
In July school holidays each year, the Abbey Medieval Festival welcomes thousands of visitors to experience life in the Middle Ages, specifically 600 to 1600AD in Europe and the Middle East. 

The Abbey Museum of Art and Archaeology together with re-enactors, jousters, performers, food vendors and merchants deliver one of Australia's premier living history events.

Tickets go on sale April 23rd 2025.
_source.productShortDescription: The Abbey Medieval Festival welcomes thousands of visitors to experience life in the Middle Ages.

The Mareeba Rodeo is one of Far North Queenslandâ€™s most iconic events, held annually in July at the renowned Kerribee Park. Since its inception in 1949, the Mareeba Rodeo has grown into a premier rodeo experience, attracting visitors from across Australia to witness thrilling rodeos, bull rides, barrel racing, and family-friendly entertainment.

Originally established to raise funds for local organisations, the event has evolved thanks to decades of hard work by dedicated committees and community members. In 1955, Mareeba hosted its first Australian Rodeo Championships, and by 1959, the beloved Rodeo Queen Competition was introduced, adding a touch of glamour to the adrenaline-fuelled festivities.

A major milestone came in 1979 when the event moved to Kerribee Park, transforming into a world-class rodeo complex with high-rise seating, modern stockyards, and state-of-the-art arena lighting. This relocation cemented Mareeba Rodeoâ€™s reputation as a must-visit outback event, combining traditional rodeo sports, sideshow alley fun, and a vibrant community atmosphere.

As it celebrates over 75 years of history, the Mareeba Rodeo continues to be a highlight of the Australian rodeo calendar, offering non-stop action, cultural heritage, and unforgettable memories. Join us in July for a true outback Queensland rodeo experience that celebrates the spirit, tradition, and community pride of Mareeba.

Mareeba Rodeo adalah salah satu acara paling ikonik di Queensland Utara Jauh, yang diadakan setiap tahun pada bulan Juli di Taman Kerribee yang terkenal. Sejak dimulai pada tahun 1949, Mareeba Rodeo telah berkembang menjadi pengalaman rodeo utama, yang menarik pengunjung dari seluruh Australia untuk menyaksikan rodeo yang mendebarkan, menunggangi banteng, balap barel, dan hiburan yang ramah keluarga.

Acara ini awalnya didirikan untuk mengumpulkan dana bagi organisasi lokal, dan telah berkembang berkat kerja keras selama puluhan tahun oleh panitia dan anggota masyarakat yang berdedikasi. Pada tahun 1955, Mareeba menjadi tuan rumah Kejuaraan Rodeo Australia pertamanya, dan pada tahun 1959, Kompetisi Ratu Rodeo yang dicintai diperkenalkan, yang menambahkan sentuhan glamor pada perayaan yang penuh adrenalin.

Tonggak sejarah utama terjadi pada tahun 1979 ketika acara tersebut dipindahkan ke Taman Kerribee, yang berubah menjadi kompleks rodeo kelas dunia dengan tempat duduk bertingkat tinggi, kandang ternak modern, dan pencahayaan arena yang canggih. Relokasi ini mengukuhkan reputasi Mareeba Rodeo sebagai acara pedalaman yang wajib dikunjungi, yang memadukan olahraga rodeo tradisional, keseruan di gang pertunjukan, dan suasana komunitas yang semarak.

Mareeba Rodeo yang merayakan lebih dari 75 tahun sejarahnya terus menjadi sorotan kalender rodeo Australia, menawarkan aksi tanpa henti, warisan budaya, dan kenangan yang tak terlupakan. Bergabunglah dengan kami pada bulan Juli untuk pengalaman rodeo Queensland pedalaman sejati yang merayakan semangat, tradisi, dan kebanggaan komunitas Mareeba.

Das Mareeba Rodeo ist eine der legendÃ¤rsten Veranstaltungen im Ã¤uÃŸersten Norden von Queensland und findet jÃ¤hrlich im Juli im berÃ¼hmten Kerribee Park statt. Seit seiner EinfÃ¼hrung im Jahr 1949 hat sich das Mareeba Rodeo zu einem erstklassigen Rodeo-Erlebnis entwickelt, das Besucher aus ganz Australien anzieht, um spannende Rodeos, Bullenreiten, Fassrennen und familienfreundliche Unterhaltung zu erleben.

UrsprÃ¼nglich ins Leben gerufen, um Geld fÃ¼r lokale Organisationen zu sammeln, hat sich die Veranstaltung dank jahrzehntelanger harter Arbeit engagierter Komitees und Gemeindemitglieder weiterentwickelt. 1955 war Mareeba Gastgeber seiner ersten australischen Rodeo-Meisterschaften, und 1959 wurde der beliebte Rodeo Queen-Wettbewerb eingefÃ¼hrt, der den adrenalingeladenen Festlichkeiten einen Hauch von Glamour verlieh.

Ein wichtiger Meilenstein wurde 1979 erreicht, als die Veranstaltung in den Kerribee Park verlegt wurde und sich in einen Rodeo-Komplex von Weltklasse mit hohen SitzplÃ¤tzen, modernen ViehhÃ¶fen und hochmoderner Arenabeleuchtung verwandelte. Dieser Umzug festigte den Ruf des Mareeba Rodeo als Outback-Event, das man unbedingt besuchen muss, und vereint traditionelle Rodeosportarten, SpaÃŸ in der Sideshow-Gasse und eine lebendige GemeinschaftsatmosphÃ¤re.

Mit seiner Ã¼ber 75-jÃ¤hrigen Geschichte ist das Mareeba Rodeo weiterhin ein HÃ¶hepunkt im australischen Rodeo-Kalender und bietet Nonstop-Action, kulturelles Erbe und unvergessliche Erinnerungen. Kommen Sie im Juli zu uns und erleben Sie ein echtes Outback-Rodeo-Erlebnis im australischen Queensland, das den Geist, die Tradition und den Gemeinschaftsstolz von Mareeba feiert.

_source.productName: NRL Titans v Broncos (Round 19) and NRLW Titans v Broncos (Round 2)
_source.productDescription:
The Gold Coast Titans are set to take on the Brisbane Broncos at Cbus Super Stadium for Round 19 of the 2025 NRL Telstra Premiership.

This clash has a reputation of selling out, so get your tickets early! With both NRL and NRLW teams taking the field, this is an afternoon of non-stop action you don't want to miss.

_source.productName: Bastille Day French Lunch at The Long Apron
_source.productDescription:
Celebrate France's national day with an elegant Bastille Day long lunch on the stunning lawns of The Long Apron â€“ a spirited nod to French tradition, with Champagne as the star of the show.

Hosted by Champagne connoisseur Bec Grimshaw, this refined afternoon will showcase exceptional sparkling wines alongside an exquisite four-course menu prepared by Head Chef Geoff Abel and his team, featuring caviar, oysters, mussels, and more.

Soak up the joie de vivre with bubbles, bites, and a relaxed French-inspired atmosphere in the heart of the Sunshine Coast Hinterland.

_source.productDescription:
Cars & Culture is coming  to Brisbane for the first time ever, and it's taking over Eat Street Northshore!

At Motor Culture Australia, they take pride in being Australia's most diverse and rewarding automotive community, with their Cars & Culture meets reflecting this.

The events are family-friendly focused and full of fun and interaction, providing like-minded people from across the region with a chance to connect with others who share the same passion for vehicles. 

Expect a fun-filled day packed with unique builds and excitement! The last event boasted over AUD100 million worth of cars and hundreds of dollars in giveaway prizes.

Here's what to expect:
Diverse Car Lineup (Super Cars, Custom Cars, JDM's, Classics, 4x4's plus  Bikes)
Attractions for all ages
Market Stalls
Live DJ
Prizes and Awards
Charity Raffle
Golden Ticket Giveaway (Win AUD20,000 Cash!)
Motor Culture Australia Giveaways
Delicious Coffee and Food (free for MCA members)

Please note: No pets are allowed at this event.

Registering for the event registers your attendance only, and does not guarantee you a car park. They recommend arriving early to secure the best spot.

Want a VIP parking spot? Send them a message with the make, model, colour and rego so they can add you to the list!

Members can redeem their free food and drink vouchers at the Motor Culture tent on the day.

_source.productName: SPARK Festival Ipswich Sip and Paint with Michelle Howarth
_source.productDescription:
Enjoy a relaxed and creative sip and paint session with local artist Michelle Howarth, including a complimentary glass of wine. Paint your own pet dog, cat, bird or any beloved companion with guidance from Michelle in a fun and supportive setting. Live music adds to the atmosphere, making this a truly enjoyable artistic escape.

Michelle Howarth is an emerging artist based in Marburg, Queensland. She is known for her peaceful and often playful artworks and prefers the flexibility of acrylics. Michelle teaches everything from casual paint and sip events to in-depth week-long classes and art tours in France with fellow artist and mentor David Hinchliffe.

This is a unique opportunity to unwind, be inspired, and enjoy a creative experience as part of SPARK Festival Ipswich.

_source.productName: Toowoomba Collectormania - Antique, Collectable and Record Fair
_source.productDescription:
Join them at the next fair - Toowoomba Antique, Collectable and Record Fair is a special opportunity to find showcase pieces for your home or to purchase unique gifts for friends and family. 

This event will be a treasure trove, filled with vendors selling items like; antique jewellery, gold, silver, coins, stamps, vintage toys, homewares, pretty porcelain, coloured glassware, uranium glass, kitchenalia, dolls, haberdashery and linen, modern collectables, oil lamps, pottery, records, man cave / shed items, vintage tools, military collectables, nautical items, retro and art deco pieces and so much more

This event is held indoors, so it makes for a fantastic family-friendly outing.
There is a cafe onsite,  with great breakfast and lunch options. ATM available.

_source.productName: Festival of Small Halls Winter Tour 2025: The Caves
_source.productDescription:
Festival of Small Halls has announced that Champagne Weather and Charm of Finches will feature on their upcoming Winter Tour 2025:Coastal Queensland.

Produced by Woodfordia Inc, veteran producers of Woodford Folk Festival, this marks the 45th tour of regional, remote and rural communities with high - quality, visionary music. The tour weaves along the coastline of Woodfordia Inc's home state, from rainforest villages to seaside towns and island escapes, each show is the pilot of the next, threading warmth and magic between.

Festival of Small Halls Winter Tour 2025 starts on the 2nd July in Cooktown, before winding down the coast finishing up in the lovely community on Macleay Island.

_source.productDescription:
The Somerset Rail Trail Classic returns for its 22nd edition on Sunday, 13 July 2025, offering a unique opportunity to run, walk, or cycle along Australiaâ€™s longest recreational rail trail. Set against the stunning backdrop of the Brisbane Valley and Brisbane River, this event welcomes participants of all abilities to enjoy an active day out in the Somerset region.

With options including a 3km or 8km run/walk and a 20km or 44km bike ride along the historic Brisbane Valley Rail Trail, it's the perfect way to challenge yourself while soaking in breathtaking scenery. Whether you're racing for a personal best or simply embracing the great outdoors with family, friends, or colleagues, the Somerset Rail Trail Classic is an event not to be missed.

_source.productDescription:
Ipswich Civic Centre and Cluster Arts presentsâ€¦ 

Proudfoot and Friends 'Blowin' in the Breeze' is coming to the Ipswich Civic Centre stage as part of our 50th Anniversary series, celebrating the rich history of performing arts across Ipswich. 

Get ready for the foot-stomping, rib-tickling, toe-tapping time of your life at the Proudfoot & Friends stage show spectacular!

Join award-winning children's performer Lucas Proudfoot on stage with his guitar, stomp box, didgeridoo and a cast of unforgettable characters on a non-stop musical adventure around Pelican Bay.

You'll meet wise, respected elder Aunty May, cheeky best friends Ned and Sis' and all their magical animal friends, like Hopa-tee-woo Kangaroo, Boompa-tee-moo Emu, Big-Gulp Pelican and everyone's favourite Ruby the Frog! But watch out for Cane Toad Bill and Fruit Bat Charlie from Smelly Mud Swamp â€“ those shady characters are always up to no goodâ€¦

Catering to 3â€“7-year-olds, this ground-breaking 45-minute musical comedy show features state-of-the-art digital puppeteering and choreographed animated projections that delight and captivate little ones (and big ones!) as proud First Nation's performer Lucas leads them on a hilarious interactive sing-along adventure.

_source.productName: Big Vibes | Sunday Session with Raw Ordio
_source.productDescription:
Get ready to light up your Sunday with big vibes, an all-ages sunday session turned neon dance party taking over The Station. This isn't your average Sunday session â€” it's a full-spectrum celebration of funk, groove, and high-energy dance music designed to leave you glowing.

Leading the charge is the unstoppable Raw Ordio, local Sunshine Coast legends bringing their signature fusion of raw funk, filthy drops and live instrumentals. If you've seen them before, you know the drill â€” if you haven't, prepare for a full-body experience!

Expect glowing lights, big beats and nothing but good times. Whether you're 15 or 50, this is your invitation to let loose and dance like nobody's watching.

They'll be throwing in food trucks, cocktails, and all their usual fun and games around The Station precinct - BI we'reis all ages, all welcome  â€” just bring your energy and ride out the weekend on the most massive high.

_source.productDescription:
A series of suburban Sunday afternoon concerts are hosted at iconic beachfront and valley locations throughout the Mackay Region. Featuring an afternoon of local music, markets, produce and fanfare, Savour the Suburbs celebrate the region's unique communities, culture and nature attractions enticing locals and visitors out of the city and into the beauty of our regional areas

The Pinnacle Cricket Ground neighbouring the Pinnacle Family Hotel, one of the most visited places in the Pioneer Valley, it the ideal valley location to spend a Sunday afternoon. Visitors can tune into local musicians and enjoy a variety of food, including the famous fresh-baked Pinnacle Pie.
_source.productShortDescription: A series of suburban Sunday afternoon concerts hosted at iconic beachfront and valley locations throughout the Mackay region.

The Somerset Rail Trail Classic returns for its 22nd edition on Sunday, 13 July 2025, offering a unique opportunity to run, walk, or cycle along Australiaâ€™s longest recreational rail trail. Set against the stunning backdrop of the Brisbane Valley and Brisbane River, this event welcomes participants of all abilities to enjoy an active day out in the Somerset region.

With options including a 3km or 8km run/walk and a 20km or 44km bike ride along the historic Brisbane Valley Rail Trail, it's the perfect way to challenge yourself while soaking in breathtaking scenery. Whether you're racing for a personal best or simply embracing the great outdoors with family, friends, or colleagues, the Somerset Rail Trail Classic is an event not to be missed.

Somerset Rail Trail Classic kembali untuk edisi ke-22 pada hari Minggu, 13 Juli 2025, menawarkan kesempatan unik untuk berlari, berjalan, atau bersepeda di sepanjang jalur kereta rekreasi terpanjang di Australia. Berlatar belakang Lembah Brisbane dan Sungai Brisbane yang menakjubkan, acara ini menyambut peserta dari semua tingkat kemampuan untuk menikmati hari yang aktif di wilayah Somerset.

Dengan pilihan termasuk lari/berjalan sejauh 3 km atau 8 km dan bersepeda sejauh 20 km atau 44 km di sepanjang Brisbane Valley Rail Trail yang bersejarah, ini adalah cara yang sempurna untuk menantang diri Anda sambil menikmati pemandangan yang menakjubkan. Baik Anda berlomba untuk mencapai rekor pribadi atau sekadar menikmati alam terbuka yang luar biasa bersama keluarga, teman, atau kolega, Somerset Rail Trail Classic adalah acara yang tidak boleh dilewatkan.
